Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging and place on a #baking tray{}. Pop on the top shelf of your oven and roast until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Chop the @medium tomatoes{2} into small 1cm pieces. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all), keeping a few sprigs to one side for garnish. Trim, then thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2} as thinly as you can. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} onto a baking tray, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden and crisp, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through. Meanwhile, place the red onion into another #bowl{}. Mix in half the @red wine vinegar{24%ml}, the @sugar{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{}. Set to one side.

Pop the chopped tomato into a large bowl. Mix in the spring onion, chopped coriander, the remaining red wine vinegar and a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with salt and pepper. Squeeze in half the @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you don't like heat, this one's very hot!). Mix to combine and set to one side.

Pop the @mayonnaise{1} into a small bowl. Mix in the remaining chipotle paste and the @water{1/2%tbsp} for the dressing. Once ready, remove the duck from the oven and use a #fork{} to pull the meat off the bone. Discard the bone.

Place the @plain taco tortillas{6} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Share the tortillas between your plates then pile everything on top! We started with the baby gem at the bottom, followed by the duck, the salsa, then the pickled onion! Finally, drizzle the mayo dressing all over the top and garnish with the leftover sprigs of coriander. Serve the sweet potato fries on the side. Dig in!

> The flavours in this dish are balanced out brilliantly with pickled onions, fresh herbs, and a chipotle mayo dressing that takes this recipe to new taste highs! A great thing to make for your next 'Taco Tuesday' or to share with friends over the weekend, this recipe will bring the warm Mexican sunshine straight to your kitchen.